"name": "5V Common-Emitter Small-Signal Amplifier",
"description": "Reusable analog block implementing a single-stage common-emitter amplifier using a 2N3904 transistor, biased from a 5 V supply, intended to amplify a 10 mV peak 1 kHz sine input to approximately 100 mV to 150 mV peak at the collector while maintaining a valid DC operating point.",
"category": "analog",
"tags": [
